# Reuse Before Create

Before adding a component, hook, utility, or helper, **search the project first**. Extend or reuse what already exists instead of duplicating logic.

## Required workflow

1. **Search** — grep or semantic search for similar names, behavior, or patterns under `src/features/`, `src/shared/`, `src/app/`.
2. **Reuse** — import from the feature's public barrel (`features/auth/index.ts`) or `shared/ui/` when it fits.
3. **Extract** — if the same logic appears in two places, extract to `shared/` or the owning feature's `hooks/` / `api/`.
4. **Create new** — only when nothing suitable exists and extraction is not warranted.

## Where to look

| Need                              | Check first                                                                                           |
| --------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Staff auth / session              | `features/auth/` — `useAuth`, guards, `staff-auth.ts`, `staff-storage.ts`                             |
| App chrome (sidebar, shell)       | `features/shell/components/`                                                                          |
| UI atoms (buttons, fields, brand) | `shared/ui/` — `PrimaryButton`, `TextField`, `Avatar`, `MandaGlyph`, `MandaWordmark`, `LoadingScreen` |
| HTTP / errors                     | `shared/api/client.ts`, `shared/api/api-error.ts`                                                     |
| Design tokens                     | `src/app/global.css` (`--manda-*`), then `shared/theme/manda-theme.ts` for TS-only use                |
| Route wiring                      | `app/router.tsx`, `app/App.tsx`                                                                       |
| Query defaults                    | `app/query-client.ts`                                                                                 |
| Electron / tokens                 | `electron/main.ts`, `electron/preload.ts` — don't duplicate IPC in renderer                           |
| Visual reference (not copy-paste) | `tmp/manda/screens-backoffice.jsx`, `tmp/manda/brand.jsx`                                             |

## Feature layout

New domain work goes in **`features/<name>/`** with the same internal shape as `auth/` and `shell/`:

```
features/kyc/
├── api/
├── components/
├── pages/
└── index.ts          # public exports for app/ and other features
```

Do **not** import another feature's internal files — use its barrel export or move shared code to `shared/`.

## Styling

- Add or extend a co-located **`*.module.css`** — don't introduce inline `style={{ … }}` for layout/theme.
- Use existing `--manda-*` CSS variables from `global.css` before adding new hex values.
- Reuse `shared/ui/` atoms before creating one-off styled elements.

## Examples

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — duplicate loading UI in a guard
if (loading) return <div style={{ height: "100vh" }}>A carregar…</div>;

// ✅ GOOD — reuse shared atom
import { LoadingScreen } from "@/shared/ui/loading-screen";
if (loading) return <LoadingScreen>A carregar…</LoadingScreen>;
```

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — raw axios in a feature page
const res = await axios.get("/staff/auth/me");

// ✅ GOOD — feature API + shared client
import { fetchMe } from "@/features/auth/api/staff-auth";
```

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — deep import into another feature's internals
import { AuthProvider } from "@/features/auth/providers/auth-provider";

// ✅ GOOD — public barrel (when exported)
import { useAuth } from "@/features/auth";
```

## When generalizing

- Prefer **one flexible component/hook** over near-identical copies.
- Keep shared APIs small; add optional params only when a second caller needs them.
- After extracting, delete the inlined duplicate and update imports.
